result.text:
New details about the @deel fundraise and its legal + private market battle with @Rippling:

-- Deel projecting $170 million-$200 million profit this year on more than $1 billion ARR
-- $650 million in shares were authorized in Deel's latest funding round, meaning this $300 million is just the first close with more $$ likely to come
-- Deel has ~$800 million of cash in the bank
-- The companies sued each other for corporate espionage; both are civil cases meaning what's at stake = potential damages and potentially costly legal fees
-- Some investors don't claim to be worried about the litigation

More information + what's next in my story with @DurotMatthew for @Forbes:

https://t.co/riqwBIlsM7
